OL,3,CBudget 2024: What do we know and what
OL,4,Cdoes it mean?
OL,6,FSir Keir Starmer has already confirmed
OL,7,Ftax rises are on the way, insisting on
OL,8,FMonday that they are necessary to
OL,9,F"prevent austerity and rebuild public
OL,10,Fservices", while higher borrowing is
OL,11,Fneeded for investment.
OL,13,FThe government insists the hikes won't
OL,14,Faffect "working people", but confusion
OL,15,Faround the definition of a "working
OL,16,Fperson" has prompted questions about
OL,17,Fwhether Labour could break its own
OL,18,Fmanifesto promise not to increase
OL,19,Fincome tax, national insurance and VAT.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/16
