OL,3,CBudget 2024: What do we know and what
OL,4,Cdoes it mean?
OL,6,FLabour committed not to raise NI
OL,7,Fduring the election campaign but the
OL,8,Fparty insists this applied to
OL,9,Femployees, rather than employers, and
OL,10,Fthis hike will not be felt by "working
OL,11,Fpeople".
OL,13,FBusinesses and charities have raised
OL,14,Fconcerns about the impact this will
OL,15,Fhave on employers already grappling
OL,16,Fwith the cost of living crisis. The
OL,17,FFederation of Small Businesses told
OL,18,FITV News it would amount to a "clear
OL,19,Fmanifesto breach" that "will hit
OL,20,Fworking people".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/16
