OL,3,CBudget 2024: What do we know and what
OL,4,Cdoes it mean?
OL,6,FIt is thought it could be raised by at
OL,7,Fleast one percentage point.
OL,9,FEmployers currently pay 13.8% on
OL,10,Fearnings above #175 a week, or #9,100
OL,11,Fa year per person, under Class 1 NI
OL,12,Fcontributions. It's deducted and set
OL,13,Faside for HMRC before wages are paid
OL,14,Fout.
OL,16,FA one percentage point increase in the
OL,17,FClass 1 rate could raise #8.45 billion
OL,18,Fover the 2025 to 2026 tax year,
OL,19,Faccording to data compiled by HMRC and
OL,20,FEY.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/16
