OL,3,CBudget 2024: What do we know and what
OL,4,Cdoes it mean?
OL,6,FThe tax which is included in the price
OL,7,Fmotorists pay for petrol at the pump
OL,8,Fcould also be raised for the first
OL,9,Ftime for more than a decade.
OL,11,FThe tax on motor fuels was frozen by
OL,12,Fthe Tories between 2010 and 2022, and
OL,13,Fthen cut by 5p to 52.95p per litre,
OL,14,Fwhere it remains.
OL,16,FIf the Labour government reversed the
OL,17,F5p cut they would raise around #2
OL,18,Fbillion.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/16
